Date: MAY 18 1977

Tribal Operations 
076.2 Elem Indian Colony

FEB 11 1977

Mr. Richard H. Burcell

Superintendent, Central California Agency

Dear Mr. Burcell:

We have reviewed the resolution adopted by members of the Elem 
Indian Colony asking that we proceed with rules of amendment 
changes, according to their Constitution and Bylaws. Their 
Constitution states that the Secretary of the Interior shall 
call an election upon their proposed language. The resolution 
is in conformity with Article IX of the band’s governing document.

As the document has never been amended, the proposal will be 
numbered Amendment I.

Proposed Amendment I would reduce the quorum required for a 
general meeting from a majority to forty-five percent (45%).

You are hereby authorized to call and conduct the necessary 
election. Voting on the constitutional amendment shall be in 
accordance with 25 CFR 52 as amended. We call your attention 
to 52.109 which provides for registration of voters.

The date of the election shall be set by you in cooperation with 
the community council and shall not be less than 20 days nor more 
than 60 days from the date of posting notices of the election.

Section 52.8 of the regulations provides for an election board 
composed of you, as chairman, and two representatives of the 
council. The election board shall furnish suitable ballots and 
supervise the conduct of the election.

This authorization, unless acted upon within 90 days from the 
date of issue, will be null and void.

The election results should be telephoned to us as soon as they 
become known. If adopted, the original of the proposed amendment 
and the completed Certificate of Results of Election should 
follow by mail for approval; but, they shall not become effective 
until approved by the Secretary of the Interior or his authorized 
representative.

(Sgd.) William E. Finale

Area Director

Enclosures

cc: Central California Agency, Tribal Ops.
 
 

