 sign-in sheet

 1995

JUL 28 1995

Mr. Thomas Brown, Chairperson
Elem Indian Colony 
P.0. Box 1968
Clearlake Oaks, California 95423

Dear Mr. Brown:

This letter will serve to provide you with an interpretation from 
the Central California Agency of specific authorities contained, in 
the Elem Indian Colony's Constitution as they pertain to the 
Executive Committee meeting held on June 5, 1995, the General 
Council meeting held on June 24, 1995, and tribal actions taken at 
these meetings.

June 5, 1995, Executive Committee Meeting

Based on our review, it appears the Executive Committee meeting of 
June 5, 1995, was conducted in accordance with the Tribe's 
Constitution and, as such, is considered to be' proper. In 
accordance with the General Council Resolution 95-06-24(C), whereby 
the Elem Indian Colony General Council delegated authority to the 
Executive Committee to enact tribal resolutions on behalf of the 
Tribe, the following comments represent an analysis of Executive 
Committee Resolutions 95-6-5(A), 95-6-5(B), 95-6-5(C), and 95-6- 
5(D).

1. 

Resolution Number 95-6-5(A)

This resolution authorizes the Executive Committee to order 
Thomas Broun and all employees of the Elem Indian Casino and 
the Elem Indian Colony to immediately provide Sarah B. Garcia, 
Tribal Secretary-Treasurer, with all financial records, 

 records of accounts, keys and combinations, and all other 

records and information to ensure that her duties are 
fulfilled in accordance with the duties of the 
secretary/treasurer contained in Article III, of the Tribe's 
Bylaws.

This resolution, as enacted, is in compliance with the 
provisions contained in the Colony's Constitution and Bylaws.

2. 

Resolution Number 95-6-5(B)

This resolution authorizes the Vice-Chairperson to apply for, 
negotiate and execute, a FY 95 Aid to Tribal Government Grant 
in Lieu of Contract and any amendments and revisions thereto.

This resolution, as enacted, appears to be not in compliance 
with the Colony's Constitution and Bylaws.

3. 

Resolution Number 95-6-5(C)

This resolution authorizes the Vice-Chairperson to apply for, 
negotiate and execute the Tribe's FY 94 ATTG Grant and any 
amendments and revisions thereto.

This resolution, as enacted, appears to be not in compliance 
with the Colony's Constitution and Bylaws.

4. 

Resolution Number 95-6-5(D)

This resolution authorizes the Vice-Chairperson to enter into 
a memorandum of agreement with the Northern California Indian 
Development Council and to apply for, negotiate and execute 
the Tribe's FY 95 Community Service Block Grant and any 
amendments and revisions thereto.

This resolution, as enacted, appears to be not in compliance 
with the Colony's Constitution and Bylaws.

June 24, 1995, General Council Meeting

It appears that this meeting was duly called. Adequate notice was 
provided to all eligible voters and a quorum was present, 
therefore, these facts, as confirmed, indicate this meeting was 
conducted in accordance with the Colony's Constitution and Bylaws.

The following represents an analysis of General Counci1 resolutions 
95-6-24(A), 95-6-24(B), and 95-6-24(C).

1. 

Resolution Number 95-6-24(A)

This resolution authorizes and directs the Secretary-Treasurer 
to take whatever steps are necessary to provide the General 
Council with an audit on all financial records of the Elem 
Indian Colony.

This resolution appears to be in compliance with the Colony's 
Constitution and Bylaws.

2. 

Resolution Number 95-6-24(B)

This resolution directs the Executive Committee, through the 
Vice-Chairperson or any duly elected successor to her office, 
to do all things necessary to enforce Executive Committee 
Resolution 95-6-5(A) against any person or entity found by 
resolution of the Executive Committee to be in violation of 
it.

This resolution further directs the Vice-Chairperson, through 
the use of the services of the Tribe's Attorney, to file a 
lawsuit in the appropriate jurisdiction against Thomas Brown 
and all persons who are in violation of Executive Committee 
Resolution 95-6-5(A).

This resolution deals directly with the internal disputes and, 
as such, the Central California Agency cannot address this 
resolution.

3. 

Resolution Number 95-6-24(C)

This resolution delegates authority to the Executive Committee 
to enact tribal resolutions.

This resolution, as enacted, appears to be in compliance with 
the Colony's Constitution and Bylaws.

If you have any questions in this matter, please contact Hr. 
Raymond Fry, Tribal Operations Officer at (916) 566-7124.

Sincerely,

/S/ Carol Rogers-Davis
 
 

FOR

 
 Harold H. Brafford
