ELEM INDIAN COLONY

GENERAL COUNCIL RESOLUTION

 
 References:

NUMBER 95-06 24 (C) 
Executive Committee to enact Resolutions

WHEREAS, Elem Indian Colony is a soveriegn Tribe, recognized by 

the Department of Interior, Bureau of Indian Affairs; 
and

WHEREAS, The General Council is the governing body of the Elem 

Indian Colony, Clearlake Oaks, California; and

WHEREAS, In accordance with the Elem Constitution, ARTICLE VII, 

POWERS OF THE GOVERNING BODY, Section 1 (h); "To 
establish its own rules of procedure for the conduct
of its affairs, and to delegate to the executive 
committee, or other representative, any of the fore
going powers"; and

WHEREAS, The General Council deems it necessary for the Elem 

Executive Committee to enact tribal resolutions for

all grant, continuing programs, meetings, memberships
of the BIA and all other entities, including all 
responsibilities and authorities imposed on the 
executive committee by the general council; now

THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED, That the General Council of the Elem 
Indian Colony, empower the Executive Committee to enact Tribal 
Resolutions.

It is hereby certified that a duly called and convened meeting 
of the Elem Indian Colony, General Council, held on June 24,
1995, with a quorum present this Resolution was approved by a
vote of 36/FOR, 0/AGAINST, and 0/ABSTAINING.

MABLE E. FOURKILLER, VICE-CHAIRPERSON

